						               													<description>Vinopolis is a game where you test your knowledge about the world of wine.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How does it work? Four professions related to wine are represented: the oenologist, the sommelier, the wine merchant, the winemaker. For each of these professions there will be questions with specific mechanics: true/false, numerical estimation within a range, positioning on a world map, multiple choice questions).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When it is the player's turn, he moves the pawn (in the shape of a bottle) to the trade of his choice, provided it is different from the previous turn, and draws a question corresponding to his neighbour. Before he answers, players can bet on his answer (success or failure) to try to win points.&amp;#10;If the person answers the question correctly, they win as many points as indicated on the card (depending on the difficulty of the question). If they answer incorrectly, they still win a chance card (which keeps the game balanced). &amp;#10;The round then moves on to the next player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;End-of-game&amp;quot; cards are placed in the 5 decks of cards (1 deck &amp;quot;chance&amp;quot;, 4 &amp;quot;questions&amp;quot; packages: one per job). When 3 &amp;quot;end-of-game&amp;quot; cards are revealed, the game ends and the player with the most points wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Affrontez-vous pour vous constituer la plus belle Cave en gagnant des Pions. Pariez et r&amp;eacute;pondez aux questions de 4 personnages exer&amp;ccedil;ant un m&amp;eacute;tier li&amp;eacute; au vin : le Vigneron, l'Oenologue, le Caviste et le Sommelier. Bluffez sur vos connaissances, pariez sur les bonnes ou mauvaises r&amp;eacute;ponses de vos adversaires et remportez la mise !&amp;#10;Et d&amp;eacute;couvrez le monde du vin gr&amp;acirc;ce aux r&amp;eacute;ponses d&amp;eacute;taill&amp;eacute;es.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the back of the box&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
